The paper deals with the problem of sorting large data sets on massively parallel machines, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses I/O requirements and communication overhead, which are important aspects of database systems, suggesting cs.DB (Databases) as another likely category. The use of multiway merging and parallelism also suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as a possible category. The paper also mentions the sorting benchmark, which is a standard measure of performance in computer science, suggesting cs.PF (Performance) as another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of algorithms, which is a core topic in computer science, suggesting cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible category.
